President Barack Obama has proclaimed May 2011 as Jewish American Heritage Month, recognizing the contributions and achievements of Jewish Americans throughout history. The proclamation highlights the resilience of Jewish refugees who sought a better future in America, as well as the enduring partnership between the United States and Israel. It also acknowledges the significant contributions of Jewish Americans in various fields, including science, literature, music, and the military. The proclamation encourages Americans to learn more about Jewish heritage and observe the month with appropriate programs and activities.